1. Action matrix:
$$M_{ij}=(\mu^2+2)\delta_{ij}-1\,(1-\delta_{ij})
=\underbrace{(\mu^2+3)}_{x}I+\underbrace{(-1)}_{y}J.$$

2. Inverse of $xI+yJ$ for size $n=3$:
$$ (xI+yJ)^{-1}=\frac1xI-\frac{y}{x(x+ny)}J. $$

3. Substitute $x=\mu^2+3$, $y=-1$, $n=3$:
$$M^{-1}=\frac1{\mu^2+3}I+\frac1{(\mu^2+3)(\mu^2)}J.$$

4. Matrix elements:
- Diagonal: 
$$M^{-1}_{11}
=\frac1{\mu^2+3}+\frac1{\mu^2(\mu^2+3)}
=\frac{\mu^2+1}{\mu^2(\mu^2+3)}.$$
- Off-diagonal:
$$M^{-1}_{12}
=\frac1{\mu^2(\mu^2+3)}.$$

5. Desired combination:
$$C
=M^{-1}_{11}-M^{-1}_{12}
=\frac{\mu^2+1}{\mu^2(\mu^2+3)}
-\frac1{\mu^2(\mu^2+3)}
=\frac{\mu^2}{\mu^2(\mu^2+3)}
=\frac1{\mu^2+3}.$$
